args: Hear me, O magical outfit!\nGrant me my royal wedding!
Mym has obtained an outfit that shows the wearer\nany illusion they desire. For her second attempt,\nshe chooses to be a royal wife.
Ah, but this mansion is amazing!\nWill it be our new love nest?
Of course. My father built it for us,\nafter all.
Aurelius built us a mansion?\nBut he once tried to kill me!
Er, but in a different world, so I suppose\nit doesn't count. Anyway, I assume your\nfather is alive and well here, yes?
He's not just MY father anymore, Mym.\nHe's also your father-in-law, and it's\nimportant for you to address him correctly.
Yes, I suppose he is that, isn't he?\nHrm, this may take some getting used to.
Heh. Well, you'll have plenty of time\nto adjust to it.
For we shall be together as husband\nand wife for the rest of our days!
I'm so happy to hear you say that, darling!
(Thank goodness THIS version of him\nis actually paying attention to me!)
(Now I can FINALLY have my ideal\nmarriage without all that other nonsense.)
Beg pardon, Your Highnesses, but\npreparations for the evening meal\nwith your guests are complete.
Thank you. We'll be right there.
You're a member of the royal family now,\nMym, which means it's time for you to\nmeet my other siblings.
You're introducing me to your siblings?!\nALL of them?!
Ha ha! You should be honored that I, the\ngreat and powerful Emile, have deigned to\ncome to meet your new bride, Brother!
And I am here as well.
I had to see what kind of a strange—\ner, I mean LOVELY—woman my brother\nhas chosen to marry.
Hrm. Well, I suppose I can manage\nif it's just these two?
My siblings are busy ruling over distant\nterritories, so it isn't often we can all\ngather in the same place.

I would have thought that to be rather
obvious, Princess...Mym, was it?
Are you that unaware of how
Alberia functions?

Here is a gold coin worth of free advice:
As a new member of the royal family,
it would behoove you to learn what is
expected of you—and quickly.
I apologize for her lack of knowledge.
Wait, why are YOU apologizing, darling?!
We're married now, which means I share\nresponsibility for your actions.
THAT'S what being married is about?!
(So if I do something improper, it will\nalso reflect poorly on my darling? Bah!\nThat doesn't make a lick of sense!)
(Still, I suppose this is the world I find\nmyself in, so I must tread carefully.)
(Right then! If they wish me to act like a\nprincess, I shall do as they desire!)
(I mean, how hard could it be?)
Alas, poor Mym didn't know the first thing\nabout royal etiquette. And as a result...

I fail to see why I must use a different
fork for each of my courses. I mean, this
big poker here will do just fine for the
salad as well as the turkey leg, yes?
Don't make sounds with my cutlery?\nWhy?
I'm so sorry, Brother. I'll talk to her later\nand make sure it doesn't happen again.
(I'm doing my best here! Why can't\nthey all see that?!)
(What does it even MEAN to be royal?!)
And yet, she does seem to be the PERFECT\nmatch for you! Ah ha! Ah ha ha ha!
I mean, who gives one whit about the\nseventh in line to the throne, anyway?
I won't stand for anyone making fun\nof my darling—ESPECIALLY YOU!
Eeek! H-how dare you speak to me in\nsuch a way, you upjumped trollop!
Oh, but these are sad times indeed when\na base peasant like yourself can join our\nmost esteemed royal family.
I don't give a damn HOW base I seem,\nOR how ＂esteemed＂ your family is!
If you were insulting ME, I could handle it.
But I won't stand for anyone speaking\nin such a way to my beloved!
Are you really so small-minded as to think\nyou can mock him simply because he was\nborn after you were? What rot!
I'll have your tongue for that, churl!

Being married to one of my brothers does
not give you a free pass to do as you like.
Perhaps you will learn this lesson after I
have my father throw you in the dungeon!
Hah! Of course you would run to daddy!\nWhat a sad, pathetic excuse for a—
Mym, stop! There's nothing to be done!\nYou just have to endure it.
I'm happy that you care about me enough\nto get this upset—I truly am.
But the royal order of succession is\nabsolute, and must never be mocked.
...I understand that even if I WAS to\nbecome your princess, I'd never be happy!

To see you suffer because of me,
and mocked simply because some
idiot was birthed into the world
before you were—it's too much!
If being part of the royal family means\nI have to endure this kind of idiocy,\nthen I want no part of it.
*sigh* And to think I thought THIS world\nwould be the one that worked.
I've tried being the salt of the earth.\nI've tried being the nobility.\nWhat else is there to try?
No, it's no good. If I can't adjust\nto the new life, I'll end up in\nthe same predicament.
What we REALLY need is a carefree life\nof ease. One where we go wherever the\nwind blows us!
If we had true love, the two of us could\ngo somewhere far away from all this.
I see now... I see our destination...\nWait for me, darling!
